[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T17:21:11+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Hispaniola from the ISS\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/KP3j-NmsICSWzDxNmv1hfm-3aaw=/0x0:720x480/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73724012/nasa_satellite_view.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://visibleearth.nasa.gov/images/152431/reflecting-on-hispaniola\" target=\"_blank\">NASA</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zokK89\">NASA is <a href=\"https://blogs.microsoft.com/blog/2024/11/14/from-questions-to-discoveries-nasas-new-earth-copilot-brings-microsoft-ai-capabilities-to-democratize-access-to-complex-data/\">teaming up with Microsoft</a> to create an AI chatbot designed to make it easier to access and understand scientific data about the Earth. The tool, called Earth Copilot, will be able to answer questions about our planet by condensing NASA\u2019s wide swath of geospatial information into easy-to-digest responses.</p>\n<p id=\"HlFPp6\">To create the tool, NASA is integrating AI into its", "id": 1518361, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296758/nasa-ai-earth-copilot-microsoft", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "NASA\u2019s AI Earth Copilot will take your questions about our planet", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T17:13:50+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-SrKDWOoDGu4ksUSj6JvQ1LHKS4=/227x0:2627x1600/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73724006/Screen_Shot_2024_09_18_at_2.07.32_PM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>The Pokemon Company</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9lHQk4\"><em>Pok\u00e9mon Trading Card Game Pocket</em> has been a big hit since its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/30/24283488/pokemon-tcg-pocket-is-finally-here\">worldwide launch last month</a>, and the team behind it has shared a brief roadmap of a couple updates to come \u2014 including the ability to trade cards with other people.</p>\n<p id=\"K8ze4o\">\u201cWe are aiming to add a feature that allows certain cards to be traded starting in January, 2025,\u201d according to an update from the team <a href=\"https://community.pokemon.com/en-us/discussion/14369/letter-to-the-community-nov-13-2024/\">on the official Pok\u00e9mon forums</a>. \u201cWe are planning to gradually expand the selection of cards that ar", "id": 1518362, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296690/pokemon-tcg-pocket-trade-cards", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pok\u00e9mon TCG Pocket will let you trade cards starting early next year", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T16:35:40+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Teenage Engineering OP-XY against a white background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ryr3Xx3C8BLmPds5t7-hFORYVyo=/0x0:3588x2392/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723954/teenageengineering1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Teenage Engineering OP-XY feels like an upgraded version of the company\u2019s six-year-old OP-Z.</em> | Image: Teenage Engineering</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RSMnyr\">Teenage Engineering\u2019s new <a href=\"https://teenage.engineering/products/op-xy\">OP-XY</a> is a portable synthesizer and sequencer that looks similar to the company\u2019s <a href=\"https://teenage.engineering/store/op-1-field/?srsltid=AfmBOooacg__9SKptrN6z36SqsSz2iNnGPNsQvYrQey68CAe6jb1ASaq\">OP\u20131 Field</a>. But functionally it\u2019s instead a more capable upgrade to the company\u2019s <a href=\"https://teenage.engineering/products/op-z\">six-year-old OP-Z</a>, with a stronger focus on layering sounds with various effects and a steeper $2,299 price", "id": 1517907, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296629/teenage-engineering-op-xy-instrument-synthesizer", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Teenage Engineering\u2019s new OP\u2013XY makes me wish I had a bigger budget for music gear", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T15:50:45+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector art of the TikTok logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZVodkScKVxTqVABgXF35o3lud1k=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723835/STK051_TIKTOK_CVirginia_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OHfva2\">TikTok will let advertisers <a href=\"https://newsroom.gettyimages.com/en/getty-images/getty-images-unlocks-premium-creative-content-for-tiktok-advertisers\">pull in content from Getty Images</a> when using the platform\u2019s AI ad creation tool. With the integration, advertisers can use Getty\u2019s licensed images and videos to make ads containing AI-generated content, including AI avatars that look like real people.</p>\n<p id=\"Gjx6ND\">The integration will be available through <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/17/24179971/tiktok-ads-ai-generated-avatars-creators-language-dubbing\">TikTok\u2019s Symphony Creative Studio</a> \u2014 an AI-powered video generation tool <a href=\"http", "id": 1517908, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296636/tiktok-ai-ads-getty-images-content", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "TikTok plugs Getty Images into its AI-generated ads and avatars", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T15:31:45+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Fenix 7S Pro on top of a green backpack\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HXB7-LURlTvA90BgnaHKSKYzcBo=/0x0:2550x1700/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723786/236729_Garmin_Fenix_7S_Pro_AKrales_0127.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>It\u2019s hard to find a fitness watch that tracks as many workouts and metrics as the Fenix 7 Pro series.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SQdYAd\">Garmin makes some of the best traditional multisport fitness watches, and one of its top models still commands a spot on our list of the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22985108/best-fitness-tracker\">best fitness trackers</a>: the <strong>Garmin Fenix 7S Pro</strong>. Now through Cyber Monday, you can get that watch for just $529.99 ($270 off) at <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wellbots.com%2Fproducts%2Fgarmin-fenix-7s-pro-solar-smartwatch&amp", "id": 1517503, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296364/garmin-fenix-7s-pro-forerunner-265-inreach-mini-2-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can save up to $270 on the Garmin Fenix 7S Pro and other Garmin watches", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T15:08:24+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A lit up Christmas tree in a living room.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ETbIErwciFXZsKapZgvMAAxpfWw=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723747/twinklylifestylepic.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Twinkly\u2019s colorful string lights are more than half off at Amazon.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"nHv7N6\">Believe it or not, but it\u2019s almost time to put up the holiday lights. If you\u2019re looking for string lights that\u2019ll really make your house stand out this year, <strong>Twinkly\u2019s Strings</strong> deliver some of the most dazzling effects available. They typically run $199.99, but right now, you can buy the 105-foot string with 400 LED lights at <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Twinkly-Strings-Christmas-Mappable-Compatible/dp/B07WGF3ZM8/?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a> for a new low of $79 thanks to an on-page coupon.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang", "id": 1517504, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296593/twinkly-strings-smart-holiday-lights-105-ft-leds-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Twinkly\u2019s smart holiday string lights have dropped to a new low price ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T15:05:02+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot of the new TMNT experience in Fortnite.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Wydp2ndP_CK9T2qdl5t7Q8dFaqw=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723732/videoframe_19120.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bOhDI8\"><em>Fortnite\u2019s</em> next big partnership with <em>Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles</em> is here. Epic Games already lets players <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/12/14/24001218/battle-royale-gets-radical\">dress up as the Turtles</a>, and now, creators can publish experiences <a href=\"https://create.fortnite.com/news/build-teenage-mutant-ninja-turtles-tmnt-islands-in-fortnite?team=personal\">built with <em>TMNT</em> assets</a> and the Unreal Editor for <em>Fortnite.</em></p>\n<p id=\"JCtjgt\">As a demonstration of what\u2019s possible, Paramount teamed up with Spiral House (which has made <a href=\"https://spiralhouse.co.uk\">other <em>Fortnite</em> experience", "id": 1517505, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296627/fortnite-tmnt-roguelike-user-made-games-creators", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Fortnite\u2019s new TMNT roguelike shows the potential for user-made games", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T13:20:01+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Dollars float through pillars, as if to exit a bank\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/H_nJDcm2ohGdzVhiL2X6y99KQF4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723474/STK417_H_Herrera_Money_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Hugo Herrera / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"npoKZB\">The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) is seeking to put Google under federal supervision, a move that could impose the same kinds of monitoring and inspections used on banks, <a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2024/11/14/cfpb-google-federal-supervision/\"><em>The Washington Post</em> reports</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"T7ddcW\">The CFPB\u2019s concerns are not totally clear and the order may still change, according to the <em>Post</em>, citing two unnamed sources. Both the agency and Google declined to comment on the report. But, plenty could change once President-elect Donald Trump reassumes office in January and pu", "id": 1516637, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296500/cfpb-google-federal-supervision", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "CFPB is reportedly trying to put Google under bank-like supervision ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T13:06:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing a 2020 Ford Explorer\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dtoOevMNU5v-Sx8zsw3dA3UdSJM=/0x0:803x535/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723435/2020_ford_explorer.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The 2020 Ford Explorer is one of the vehicles affected by the recall.</em> | Image: Ford</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"gMAjrt\">Ford has agreed to <a href=\"https://www.nhtsa.gov/press-releases/ford-consent-order-165-million-civil-penalty\">pay a fine that could go up to $165 million</a> after the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration found the automaker took too long to recall vehicles with faulty rearview cameras and failed to \u201cprovide accurate and complete recall information.\u201d. This penalty is the second largest, only <a href=\"https://www.cbsnews.com/news/takata-fined-up-to-200-million-for-air-bag-bungle/\">behind the $200 million</a> Takata was ordered to pay.</p>\n<p id=\"vORxMH\"><a href=\"https://www.caranddriv", "id": 1516638, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296494/ford-nhtsa-recall-fine-rearview-camera", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Ford penalized $165 million over moving too slowly on a rearview camera recall", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T13:00:13+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Richard Ramsay opening the Nike Elite EasyOn backpack.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/fvTITUvBAvOOJsfy_cYQJIv8OuM=/0x0:3240x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723421/nike1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The fabric interior of Nike\u2019s Elite EasyOn backpack is printed with instructions on how to use and customize it.</em> | Image: Nike</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Eg0cHI\">Nike\u2019s new Elite EasyOn backpack was <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fabout.nike.com%2Fen%2Fstories%2Fnike-elite-easy-on-backpack&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F11%2F14%2F24296456%2Fnike-elite-easyon-backpack-design-accessibility-paralympics\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">designed with innovative features</a> making it accessible for as many athletes as possible, including those with low dexterity or motor skills. Originally devel", "id": 1516639, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296456/nike-elite-easyon-backpack-design-accessibility-paralympics", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Nike\u2019s new easy open backpack was designed to prioritize accessibility", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T12:54:42+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Bluesky logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/EmavTkU0i30OHHXUecr668hcGig=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723380/STK133_BLUESKY__B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"vOuec0\">Bluesky is growing quickly in popularity, but if you\u2019re trying to use it today, the site might be acting up. As I was writing this article, my feeds and notifications were <em>very</em> slow to load on the web and mobile while logged in, and that has similarly been the case for a few of my <em>Verge</em> colleagues. </p>\n<p id=\"bgWude\">Things seem to be working now, but Bluesky developers have already warned that things might not work as expected today. Earlier this morning, developer Samuel Newman shared that the site would be briefly going into read-only mode <a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/samuel.bsky.team/post/3lavxscoacc23\">because \u201csomethin", "id": 1516640, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296537/bluesky-acting-up-outage-down", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Bluesky has been acting up today", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T12:35:45+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Google\u2019s wordmark, written in red and pink on a dark blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pJ5KAmyvk-SZ8AhDvIlK7LSYySo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723316/STK093_Google_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"IZrQw9\">Google has announced it will stop showing political ads to users in the European Union next year due to uncertainties around the bloc\u2019s new transparency regulations. <a href=\"https://blog.google/around-the-globe/google-europe/political-advertising-in-eu/\">In a new blog post</a>, Google says the upcoming <a href=\"https://www.europarl.europa.eu/news/en/press-room/20240223IPR18071/parliament-adopts-new-transparency-rules-for-political-advertising\">Transparency and Targeting of Political Advertising (TTPA) rules</a> that aim to prevent election interference and help voters make informed choices will introduce signific", "id": 1516641, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296510/google-dropping-political-ads-in-the-eu-ttpa", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google says it will stop serving political ads in the EU", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T11:56:41+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A woman in a red shirt flanked by another woman in a black dress and a man wearing a sweater over a blur shirt.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/26QdsPCwr9dq_A5Kqjr5cP1MlXE=/325x0:2017x1128/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723202/MythicQuestS4.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Apple TV Plus</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"E0xeBx\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/10/21/22738881/mythic-quest-renewed-season-three-four-apple-tv-plus\"><em>Mythic Quest</em>\u2019s upcoming fourth season</a> finally has a release date, but Apple\u2019s future plans for the series aren\u2019t stopping there.</p>\n<p id=\"TmN6lL\">Today, <a href=\"https://www.apple.com/tv-pr/news/2024/11/apples-acclaimed-workplace-comedy-mythic-quest-returns-for-season-four-wednesday-january-29-on-apple-tv/\">Apple announced</a> that <em>Mythic Quest </em>will return on January 29th with a two-episode premiere picking up Ian Grimm (Rob McElhenney,) Poppy Li (Charlotte Nicdao,) Dav", "id": 1516154, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296445/mythic-quest-season-4-premiere-date-side-quest", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Mythic Quest is getting a spinoff anthology series", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T11:55:54+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/p-L5sTHjfOa4vww9ZzZyiNqhAVM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723199/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"CQ1J4TN8G-1731599487.379669-thread-list-Thread_1731601012.755289\">Bluesky might be on the rise, but Instagram and Threads boss Adam Mosseri wants you to know that Threads is still much bigger. In a post on Thursday, Mosseri <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@mosseri/post/DCWz7LSvA36?xmt=AQGz7FdXZylT7TzCBHKUZQaewk9QgRE_cyAou_iNmhQ49w\">said that</a> Threads has gotten \u201cmore than 15 million signups in November alone,\u201d seemingly trying to throw some cold water over Bluesky crossing <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/13/24295484/bluesky-15-million-users-social-media-x-musk\">15 million users total on Wednesday</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"U920Ju\">Mosseri also reiterated that ", "id": 1516155, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296490/meta-threads-15-million-adam-mosseri-bluesky", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Threads grew by a Bluesky this month", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T11:43:36+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Arc logo on pink and blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2BH4U7f189oHE0AorDsL_873N4A=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73723160/STK283_ARC_BROWSER_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"z3T2Jp\">After an <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/4/24262056/arc-search-android-beta-mobile-web-browser\">open beta</a> that rolled out last month, Arc Search is now available to all Android users. The Browser Company\u2019s search engine \u2014 which describes itself as \u201cthe fastest way to search\u201d \u2014 has been positioning itself as a better alternative to Chrome.</p>\n<p id=\"8yoqDB\">Arc Search not only blocks ads but also has an AI feature called \u201cbrowse for me\u201d that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/28/24053882/arc-search-browser-web-app-ios\">summarizes search results</a>. In a September <em>Decoder</em> interview, Browser Company CEO Josh Mille", "id": 1516156, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296473/arc-search-android-mobile-web-browser-launch", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Arc\u2019s mobile browser is now available to everyone on Android", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:42:03+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Xbox logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g7yDV375ukSWfYhqv8vwFrIUgS0=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722997/STK048_XBOX_C.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ieflp0\">Microsoft has been trying to expand Xbox to multiple devices for <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/6/11/18661247/phil-spencer-interview-xbox-project-scarlett-xcloud-e3-2019\">more than five years now</a>, and now it\u2019s launching a marketing campaign to make it very clear that it thinks every screen is an Xbox now. A new \u201cThis is an Xbox\u201d <a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/11/14/this-is-an-xbox/\">campaign is launching today</a> to position the Xbox brand as a way to play games across multiple devices, instead of just an Xbox console.</p>\n<p id=\"BTU5G1\">\u201cThis Is an Xbox invites people to play with Xbox across multiple devices and screens,\u201d explains Craig McNary,", "id": 1515649, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296420/microsoft-this-is-an-xbox-marketing-campaign-xbox-everywhere", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Xbox\u00a0continues its push beyond consoles with new ad campaign", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:15:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"CD\u2019s hanging on fishhooks to represent AI scam albums.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_csE4Q3WMgAHGJB5k2pYZIJqHBc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722938/247377_AI_scam_albums_CVirginiaA.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Cath Virginia / The Verge, Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>How fake music targets real artists.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24294995/spotify-ai-fake-albums-scam-distributors-metadata\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1515650, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24294995/spotify-ai-fake-albums-scam-distributors-metadata", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Not even Spotify is safe from AI slop", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:10:26+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Facebook logo surrounded by blue dots and white squiggles.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7eDAIlRogNzn9L4GkoJ3IQZoq90=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722926/STK040_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_4_facebook.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"jCbwzX\">Almost two years after <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/commission/presscorner/detail/en/ip_22_7728\">EU regulators first accused Meta of \u201cabusive practices\u201d</a> that gave the tech giant unfair market advantages, <a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/commission/presscorner/detail/en/ip_24_5801\">the European Commission has fined Meta</a> \u20ac797.7 million (around $840 million). The combination of forcing Facebook users to be exposed to Marketplace and imposing restrictions against third-party classified ads providers on the platform are the two main reasons cited for the fine.</p>\n<p id=\"s8Mrwt\">In a statement, the EU", "id": 1515651, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296391/meta-facebook-marketplace-840-million-eu-fine", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta hit with $840 million fine for linking Facebook and Marketplace", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:01:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A bunch of cassette players and CD players on a table, including new models from Fiio and We Are Rewind.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ecCtGbY5Wga8qdGqL13nynIdlOc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722899/VRG_Retro_Music_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"X3ZLAb\">Cassette tape sales are at <a href=\"https://www.nme.com/news/music/cassette-tape-sales-at-20-year-high-3432784\">a 20-year high</a>, the vinyl market is on a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/26/24112369/riaa-2023-music-revenue-streaming-vinyl-cds-physical-media\">17-year growth streak</a>, and CDs have <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2024/01/06/gen-z-cds-buying-collection\">caught the attention of Gen Z</a>. After a resurgence of retro physical media, tech companies have now jumped in to provide new hardware to play these formats. </p>\n<p id=\"np2OJN\">Companies like We Are Rewind, Fiio, and ", "id": 1515652, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24295971/we-are-rewind-fiio-cassette-player-cd-dm-13", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Why are cassette and CD players so bulky now? ", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Elon Musk and Donald Trump collaged together with Teslas in the background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XZh4vH3dRi0NooZSo5TuYVjaH2M=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722850/DCD_Trump_Elon.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>What Elon Musk really wants from a Trump presidency.&nbsp;</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24296301/elon-musk-donald-trump-tesla-evs-climate-change-auto-industry-tariffs-decoder-podcast\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1515189, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24296301/elon-musk-donald-trump-tesla-evs-climate-change-auto-industry-tariffs-decoder-podcast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Trump\u2019s second term could be bad for EVs \u2014 but great for Tesla", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T10:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"Various gifts for tinkerers arranged in a vivid scene.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SuP0q0e2PKjqe2XFpxKPgyK-SkA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722858/247215_Holiday_GG_2024_AKrales_TINKERLEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Whether you\u2019re assembling a PC, planning an epic Etsy crafts store, or just fixing a squeaky old chair, we found some handy tools that anyone can appreciate.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24224047/best-tool-gift-ideas-holiday-2024-handyperson-builders-tinkerers\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>\n\n", "id": 1515190, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24224047/best-tool-gift-ideas-holiday-2024-handyperson-builders-tinkerers", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Verge\u2019s 2024 holiday gift guide for tinkerers", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T09:47:31+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"YouTube logo image in red over a geometric red, black, and cream background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZEIBjRDvI-HE-5oeZ4nhJoaK4DA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722823/acastro_STK092_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"7D0KRF\">YouTube is taking a page out of the TikTok playbook by adding \u201cjewels\u201d you buy to <a href=\"https://support.google.com/youtube/thread/307754858?hl=en\">exchange for gifts for your favorite creators</a> during livestreams. The feature, announced in September\u2019s Made on YouTube event, is rolling out in the US over the next few weeks for eligible creators in the YouTube Partner Program.</p>\n<p id=\"AUNnVS\">The feature is reminiscent of TikTok\u2019s livestream gifting, which essentially works the same way, except you buy \u201ccoins.\u201d On YouTube, gifts you send to live streamers appear onscreen and add to their earnings cal", "id": 1515191, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296327/youtube-livestream-gifts-jewels", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "YouTube is getting in on the digital gifting game", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T09:20:10+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Disney Plus logo on a blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FLiKe-swToj7uHPnPpC7b7x415w=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722784/STK080_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_5_disney_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8opepf\">Disney made money off its streaming business for the second time in a row. <a href=\"https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/app/uploads/2024/11/q4-fy24-earnings.pdf\">During Q4 2024</a>, profit from Disney Plus, Hulu, and ESPN Plus soared to $321 million, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24214898/disney-streaming-business-profitable-earnings-q3-2024\">up from $47 million last quarter</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"HwqcGG\">During an earnings call on Thursday, Disney CEO Bob Iger said around 60 percent of all new subscribers are choosing Disney Plus\u2019s ad-supported plan. Meanwhile, 37 percent of total subscribers in the US are cur", "id": 1515192, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296307/disney-plus-streaming-business-profit-q4-2024-earnings", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Disney\u2019s streaming business is finally finding its footing", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T09:00:16+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A marketing photo of Amazon\u2019s Fire TV Omni Mini-LED series TV.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/LMFQY7QSt3Y2y07ZLQGiUZzNH2w=/1x0:1792x1194/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722745/Fire_TV_Omni_Mini_LED_Series_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"r66xt2\">Amazon is today introducing its latest Fire TV Omni TV series, and it\u2019s the first to feature Mini LED backlighting for improved contrast, less blooming, and greater brightness than past models. The \u201cFire TV Omni Mini-LED Series\u201d features up to 1,344 dimming zones (depending on screen size) and delivers up to 1,400 nits of peak brightness. That\u2019s respectable, but falls short of top Mini LED contenders like <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/TCL-75QM851G-Accelerator-Streaming-Television/dp/B0CZM95SG6?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">TCL\u2019s QM8</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Hisense-65-Inch-Mini", "id": 1515193, "language": null, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/14/24296334/amazon-fire-tv-omni-mini-led-features-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 359, "source_url": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon announces its first Mini LED Fire TV \u2014 and this one\u2019s also built for gaming", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-14T09:00:00+00:00", "description": "  \n\n    <figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Words With Friends on a smartphone.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/y3IUxfOQStQFTtKtJ933pU1lxWU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73722693/akrales_171107_2126_0032.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KejWJq\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23660809/wordle-new-york-times-interview-zoe-bell-gdc-2023\"><em>Wordle</em>\u2019s success</a> has caused <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/10/25/24279439/news-games-crossword-wordle\">an explosion in newspaper-style puzzle games</a>, and now <em>Words With Friends</em> is getting in on the action. The long-running word game is adding four solo modes that can be played daily, and they\u2019ll sound familiar to those who use <em>The</em> <em>New York Times\u2019</em> gaming app.</p>\n<p id=\"mgcAhv\">The new games include a m